e-and-search/021-cooperative-heavy-phases/tasks.md\",\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/021-cooperative-heavy-phases/implementation-summary.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/trigger-embedding-backfill.vitest.ts\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/handler-memory-index-scan-jobs.vitest.ts\",\".opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/maintenance-marker.ts\"],\"findingsCount\":1,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":1,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":1,\"P2\":0},\"findingsRefined\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[{\"findingId\":\"F001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"category\":\"correctness\",\"status\":\"active\",\"dimension\":\"correctness\",\"title\":\"Trigger backfill still has an unbounded synchronous pre-chunk SELECT\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts\",\"line\":173,\"lineRange\":\"173-180\",\"finding_class\":\"contract_safety\",\"description\":\"REQ-002 says the trigger backfill can never block the loop, but the implementation still loads every eligible memory row with a synchronous .all() before the first cancellation check or chunk yield. The write transaction is chunked, but the pre-chunk read remains corpus-sized, non-cancellable synchronous work.\",\"evidence\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/021-cooperative-heavy-phases/spec.md:132-134\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts:173-180\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts:262-278\"],\"content_hash\":\"bf6fbea0db8088d7588ca100c51b2f596cb17c7180fe69066cae95e3beaff635\",\"confidence\":0.84}],\"newFindingsRatio\":1,\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":\"Correctness pass only. Core traceability was not fully covered because maxIterations=1 and checklist.md is absent from the target Level 1 packet.\",\"results\":[{\"protocolId\":\"spec_code\",\"status\":\"partial\",\"gateClass\":\"hard\",\"applicable\":true,\"counts\":{\"pass\":3,\"partial\":1,\"fail\":0,\"skipped\":0},\"evidence\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/021-cooperative-heavy-phases/spec.md:132-134\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts:173-180\"],\"findingRefs\":[\"F001\"],\"summary\":\"Most sampled implementation claims resolve, but REQ-002 remains partially unmet by the pre-chunk full-corpus SELECT.\"},{\"protocolId\":\"checklist_evidence\",\"status\":\"partial\",\"gateClass\":\"hard\",\"applicable\":true,\"counts\":{\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"skipped\":1},\"evidence\":[],\"findingRefs\":[],\"summary\":\"Target packet has no checklist.md; Level 1 packet, so no checklist marks were available to validate.\"}]},\"coverage\":{\"dimensionsCovered\":[\"correctness\"],\"dimensionsMissing\":[\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"],\"dimensionCoverage\":0.25,\"requiredProtocolsCovered\":false,\"filesReviewedCount\":10},\"noveltyJustification\":\"One new contract-safety issue found by comparing REQ-002 against the actual trigger backfill control flow.\",\"ruledOut\":[\"Launcher adoption root cause: launcher paths read the fresh maintenance marker before respawn/reap and adopt busy daemons as specified.\",\"Missing marker refresh on timed tail phases: both empty-files and main scan branches enter orphan-sweep, enrichment-repair, trigger-backfill, and near-dup-repair through timedPhase/onPhase.\"],\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-p021-1781754954084-qylfz6\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-18T03:59:56Z\",\"durationMs\":0,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\",\"session\":\"current-fanout-lineage\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":1,\"passed\":true,\"packets\":[{\"findingId\":\"F001\",\"claim\":\"Trigger backfill still performs an unbounded synchronous full-corpus SELECT before its first cancellation/yield boundary, so REQ-002's never-block/cancellable claim is not fully satisfied.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/021-cooperative-heavy-phases/spec.md:132-134\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts:173-180\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts:262-278\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Reviewed the subsequent phrase-sync chunk loop, cache-hit yield path, cancellation tests, timedPhase scan wiring, and launcher marker-adoption code. The write transaction is chunked and the launcher behavior is correct, but no pagination or cancellation check exists before sourceRows = ...all().\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"The current corpus may be small enough that the SELECT is fast in practice, and the spec text names the whole-corpus transaction specifically. That does not fully satisfy the stronger acceptance wording that the trigger backfill can never block the loop when enabled.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.84,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade or close if the source-row read is paginated/limited with cancellation and yield boundaries, or if a documented hard cap plus regression test proves the SELECT cannot materially block the event loop.\",\"transitions\":[{\"iteration\":1,\"from\":null,\"to\":\"P1\",\"reason\":\"Initial discovery during correctness review.\"}]}],\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-18T03:59:56Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-p021-1781754954084-qylfz